<p>13:  Left camp at 3 a.m. &amp; loaded trucks with wagons &amp; horses, pulling out at 7 a.m.   Reached Minia (197 miles) at 4 p.m., camping near the town.  Branch of the Nile running through the camp but teeming with bellhasia  germs &amp; unfit for human use.</p>
<p>14:  Went to town, rather decent &amp; visited Coptic church with two merchants, who took me to dinner &amp; sight seeing per gharry.</p>
<p>17:  Left Minia for Pamlit el Abid with 2nd  regt.  Good camp &amp; people treat us very well.</p>
<p>18:  Water is drawn from the "Yusef" &amp; as the niggers bathe in it, we have to boil the water before drinking it.  Dead animals also float by our camp, but it is the only water available.</p>
<p>22:  Two bellhasia patients sent away to Minia.  Doctors busy</p>
